check-pen
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a small yard in a set of sheep-yards where sheep are held and examined for mistakes in drafting, or for inspection or treatment.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
